Developers write their unit tests to test their java code using a unit testing FW as follows:

testNG(Testing New Generation)-->unit testing framework
(testNG is built on top of JUNIT and has more advanced and user friendly features than JUNIT)
(Automation engineers prefer testNG wrt to Junit)

JUNIT
(TestNG or JUNIT cannot be used for unit testing of code in other languages but only used for unit testing of java code)

PyTest -- Python unit testing FW
PHPUnit	--	PHP unit testing FW
NUnit -- .Net unit testing FW
Mocha/Jasmine	--	Javascript unit testing FW
RubyUnit	--	Ruby testing FW

Purpose->to write testcases	+	assertions(validations)	+	HTML reports	+	other features
